double two = 2.0;
cout << ( seven / two ) << endl;
```

Or you can type cast one or both of the variables:
```c++
int seven = 7;
int two = 2;
cout << ( (double) seven / (double) two ) << endl;
```

Alternatively, you can convert `string` variables to doubles:
```c++
string seven = "7";
string two = "2";
cout << ( stod(seven) / stod(two) );
```

